reviews.review: AWESOME!!!!  Marvelous end to the Star Wars storyline.  Great to see some of the most endearing past characters again.  A must see for all Star Wars fans!
Super with all the elements from the past!
Very disappointed.  The story just doesn't make any sense for the part that the Emperor all in a sudden reappeared in this episode.
Very nice ending to the saga.
Some parts are confusing and less than explained, but overall the movie is very good.

It was a good movie all and all. It was just a lil but predictable after awhile and not nearly enough action or suspense like the older ones. The plot twist at the end was also predictable but I still enjoyed the movie being a big fan and what not.
Great ending to the saga I’ve been following from 1977 on. Don’t understand the negative reviews. It wasn’t perfect but it’s much better than critics say.

The movie was great. I like all of the Star Wars movies. Adding Leia in was choppy. But I think they did the best they could with her passing. The 40 minutes of previews was out of hand. The move was to start at 2:50. It started at 3:30. Most ridiculous!!
I thought it was a good ending to the Skywalker story. If 8 hadn't been so bad in think they could've had a more flushed out 9.

JJ Abrams had an almost impossible task ahead of him, make logical sense of this trilogy and at the same time give a satisfying ending to the whole saga. For this reason i don't blame him too much. The only real criticism that I would like to make regards his obvious lack of creativity, already put on display in The Force Awakens. 

Of course throughout the movie but especially at the beginning the pacing is too tight. Everything happens super fast without giving the viewer the time to better absorb what is going on. There are many things that didn't work, many things that don't make sense and others that had to be done much better, still that's also a lot to like in this movie. I won't spoil anything. 

I didn't hate it, i think it's way more rewatchable than The Last Jedi, The Phantom Menace and Attack of the Clones, but at the end the question i asked myself was: "what was the point of this trilogy?" 

Rise of Skywalker is beautiful to watch, the special effects are good as well as the cinematography but it lacks any emotion thanks to what came before. This was a disjointed trilogy that didn't make the viewer care about the characters and what's happening. A huge opportunity lost by Lucas Film and Disney. That's why episode IX and the final chapter of the Skywalker saga it's only a 2,5 stars out of 5. Meh, it passed the time. Literally.
